<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Acceptable Use Policy</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-50">
    <div class="min-h-screen py-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Acceptable Use Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: November 2025 | Applicable Law: State of Utah</p>

                <div class="prose max-w-none space-y-6">
                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. General Conduct</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            All users must conduct themselves in a respectful, professional, and appropriate manner.
                            This platform is designed to support a positive learning and competitive environment that
                            fosters creativity, collaboration, and innovation.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Users are expected to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Treat all participants, judges, administrators, and volunteers with respect and courtesy
                            </li>
                            <li>Engage constructively in all interactions and communications</li>
                            <li>Promote an inclusive environment that welcomes participants of all backgrounds, skill
                                levels, and identities</li>
                            <li>Use the platform and event facilities responsibly and as intended</li>
                            <li>Follow instructions from event staff and administrators promptly</li>
                            <li>Represent themselves and their teams honestly and ethically</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Prohibited Content</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You may not submit, post, display, or share content that:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Contains profanity, vulgarity, obscenity, or offensive language</li>
                            <li>Includes hate speech, slurs, or discriminatory language based on race, ethnicity,
                                national origin, religion, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, disability,
                                or any other protected characteristic</li>
                            <li>Is defamatory, libelous, harassing, threatening, bullying, or intimidating</li>
                            <li>Violates intellectual property rights, including copyrights, trademarks, patents, or
                                trade secrets</li>
                            <li>Contains malware, viruses, worms, Trojan horses, ransomware, spyware, or any other
                                malicious code</li>
                            <li>Is illegal under federal, state, or local law, or promotes illegal activities</li>
                            <li>Is sexually explicit, pornographic, or otherwise inappropriate for a youth-inclusive
                                educational environment</li>
                            <li>Contains personal information of others without their explicit consent (including names,
                                addresses, phone numbers, social security numbers, or financial information)</li>
                            <li>Promotes violence, self-harm, dangerous activities, or substance abuse</li>
                            <li>Contains false, misleading, or deceptive information</li>
                            <li>Infringes on privacy rights or violates confidentiality agreements</li>
                            <li>Contains political campaign materials or partisan political advocacy</li>
                            <li>Includes spam, unsolicited advertising, or commercial solicitation</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Team Names and Project Names</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Team names, project names, and all other user-generated identifiers must be:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Appropriate and professional for an educational, all-ages environment</li>
                            <li>Free of profanity, sexual references, drug references, and offensive language</li>
                            <li>Not misleading, deceptive, or impersonating other teams, organizations, or individuals
                            </li>
                            <li>Respectful of all participants and not targeting or mocking any individual or group</li>
                            <li>Not containing trademarks or brand names unless you have explicit authorization</li>
                            <li>Compliant with all other content guidelines in this policy</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Event administrators reserve the right to require changes to any team or project name that
                            violates these guidelines. Failure to comply may result in disqualification.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Competition Integrity</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You agree to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Submit only original work or properly attributed and licensed content</li>
                            <li>Clearly identify and attribute any third-party code, libraries, frameworks, assets, or
                                resources used in your project</li>
                            <li>Not engage in cheating, plagiarism, fraud, or any form of academic dishonesty</li>
                            <li>Follow all competition rules, guidelines, and time constraints</li>
                            <li>Respect the judging process, criteria, and final decisions</li>
                            <li>Not attempt to manipulate scores, rankings, or voting systems</li>
                            <li>Not collude with other teams to gain unfair advantages</li>
                            <li>Not sabotage or interfere with other teams' projects or presentations</li>
                            <li>Disclose any conflicts of interest (e.g., personal relationships with judges)</li>
                            <li>Use only permitted resources, tools, and assistance during the competition</li>
                            <li>Complete all required elements of the competition (registration, presentations,
                                demonstrations, etc.)</li>
                            <li>Be present and actively participate during all mandatory portions of the event</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Open Source and Third-Party Code:</strong> While the use of open-source libraries,
                            frameworks, and code snippets is generally permitted, teams must clearly document all
                            third-party resources used. The originality and creativity of your implementation and
                            application of these resources will be considered during judging. Projects that are
                            predominantly third-party code with minimal original contribution may be disqualified or
                            receive reduced scores.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. System Security and Technical Conduct
                        </h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You may not:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the platform, systems, networks, or accounts</li>
                            <li>Interfere with, disrupt, or compromise the platform's operation or availability</li>
                            <li>Use automated systems, bots, scrapers, or scripts to access the platform without
                                explicit permission</li>
                            <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, or derive source code from the
                                platform</li>
                            <li>Probe, scan, or test the security or vulnerabilities of the platform without
                                authorization</li>
                            <li>Bypass, circumvent, or attempt to bypass any security measures, authentication
                                mechanisms, or access controls</li>
                            <li>Launch denial-of-service attacks or flood the system with requests</li>
                            <li>Inject malicious code, scripts, or commands (SQL injection, XSS, etc.)</li>
                            <li>Access or attempt to access areas of the platform for which you do not have
                                authorization</li>
                            <li>Share, transfer, or sell your account credentials to others</li>
                            <li>Create multiple accounts to circumvent restrictions or gain unfair advantages</li>
                            <li>Use the platform to distribute malware or conduct phishing attacks</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Responsible Disclosure:</strong> If you discover a security vulnerability, you must
                            report it immediately to event administrators through official channels. Do not exploit,
                            share, or publicize vulnerabilities. We appreciate responsible security researchers and will
                            work with you to address legitimate security concerns.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Privacy and Data Protection</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You must:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Respect the privacy of all users, participants, judges, and staff</li>
                            <li>Not collect, store, use, or disclose other users' personal data without explicit consent
                            </li>
                            <li>Not share your account credentials with others or allow unauthorized access to your
                                account</li>
                            <li>Maintain the confidentiality of any non-public information you may access</li>
                            <li>Report any privacy violations or data breaches immediately to administrators</li>
                            <li>Report any security vulnerabilities through proper channels</li>
                            <li>Not record, photograph, or livestream other participants without their consent</li>
                            <li>Comply with all applicable privacy laws and regulations, including COPPA (Children's
                                Online Privacy Protection Act) and Utah privacy laws</li>
                            <li>Not use information obtained through the platform for any purpose other than
                                participating in the event</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Minors' Privacy:</strong> Special care must be taken when interacting with or about
                            participants under 18. Do not attempt to collect personal information from minors, and
                            report any concerning behavior to event staff immediately.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. Physical Event Conduct</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            At in-person events, you must:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Follow all venue rules, regulations, and safety procedures</li>
                            <li>Respect event staff, security personnel, and venue employees</li>
                            <li>Not engage in any illegal activities on event premises</li>
                            <li>Not bring weapons, illegal substances, or other prohibited items to the venue</li>
                            <li>Not consume alcohol or use controlled substances during the event (regardless of age or
                                legal status)</li>
                            <li>Maintain appropriate physical boundaries and personal space</li>
                            <li>Report any safety concerns, emergencies, or suspicious behavior immediately</li>
                            <li>Use event facilities and equipment responsibly and as intended</li>
                            <li>Clean up your workspace and dispose of trash properly</li>
                            <li>Follow COVID-19 or other health and safety protocols in effect</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You agree to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Respect all intellectual property rights, including patents, copyrights, trademarks, and
                                trade secrets</li>
                            <li>Not submit content that infringes on others' intellectual property</li>
                            <li>Provide proper attribution for all third-party content, code, libraries, and resources
                            </li>
                            <li>Ensure you have the right to use, display, and submit all content in your project</li>
                            <li>Not reverse engineer or copy other teams' projects</li>
                            <li>Understand that you retain ownership of your original work, subject to the license
                                granted in the Terms of Use</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Prohibited Uses of Technology</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            You may not use the platform or event resources to:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Mine cryptocurrency or conduct blockchain transactions</li>
                            <li>Run computationally intensive tasks unrelated to your project</li>
                            <li>Host or distribute pirated software, media, or other unauthorized content</li>
                            <li>Conduct penetration testing or security assessments on external systems</li>
                            <li>Spam, phish, or conduct social engineering attacks</li>
                            <li>Operate proxy servers or VPN services</li>
                            <li>Scrape or harvest data from third-party websites without authorization</li>
                            <li>Generate, store, or transmit illegal content</li>
                        </ul>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. Enforcement and Violations</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            Violations of this Acceptable Use Policy may result in one or more of the following actions,
                            at the sole discretion of event administrators:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li><strong>Warning:</strong> Verbal or written notice of the violation</li>
                            <li><strong>Content Removal:</strong> Removal of offending content, team names, or project
                                materials</li>
                            <li><strong>Temporary Suspension:</strong> Temporary restriction of platform access or event
                                participation</li>
                            <li><strong>Permanent Ban:</strong> Permanent removal from the platform and prohibition from
                                future events</li>
                            <li><strong>Disqualification:</strong> Removal from competition and ineligibility for prizes
                                or recognition</li>
                            <li><strong>Legal Action:</strong> Referral to law enforcement or pursuit of civil remedies
                                for serious violations</li>
                            <li><strong>Forfeiture of Prizes:</strong> Return of any prizes, awards, or recognition
                                received</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            The severity of the response will depend on the nature, frequency, and impact of the
                            violation. Event administrators reserve the right to take immediate action without prior
                            warning for serious violations that pose a threat to safety, security, or the integrity of
                            the event.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            <strong>Appeals Process:</strong> If you believe an enforcement action was taken in error,
                            you may submit a written appeal to event administrators within 7 days of the action. Appeals
                            will be reviewed, but enforcement decisions are generally final.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">11. Reporting Violations</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            If you witness or experience a violation of this policy, please report it immediately to
                            event administrators through one of the following methods:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Speak to any event staff member in person at the event venue</li>
                            <li>Contact event administrators using the contact information provided during event
                                registration</li>
                            <li>For questions or concerns, reach out to event administrators through the contact methods
                                provided at registration</li>
                            <li>For emergencies or safety concerns, contact venue security or call 911</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            When reporting a violation, please provide:
                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
                            <li>Your name and contact information</li>
                            <li>Description of the incident or violation</li>
                            <li>Date, time, and location (if applicable)</li>
                            <li>Names or identifiers of individuals involved</li>
                            <li>Any evidence (screenshots, photos, messages, etc.)</li>
                            <li>Names of any witnesses</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            All reports will be taken seriously and investigated promptly. We are committed to
                            maintaining a safe, respectful environment and will not tolerate retaliation against
                            individuals who report violations in good faith.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">12. Modifications to This Policy</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            We reserve the right to modify this Acceptable Use Policy at any time. Changes will be
                            effective immediately upon posting to the platform. Continued use of the platform or
                            participation in the event after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the modified
                            policy. It is your responsibility to review this policy periodically for updates.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">13. Jurisdiction and Governing Law</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            This Acceptable Use Policy is governed by the laws of the State of Utah, without regard to
                            its conflict of law provisions. Any disputes arising from or relating to this policy shall
                            be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Utah.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">14. Contact Information</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            For questions about this Acceptable Use Policy or to report violations, please contact the
                            event administrators using the contact information provided during event registration. You
                            can also speak with event staff in person at the event venue.
                        </p>
                    </section>

                    <section>
                        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">15. Acknowledgment</h2>
                        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                            By using this platform and participating in this event, you acknowledge that you have read,
                            understood, and agree to be bound by this Acceptable Use Policy. You further acknowledge
                            that violation of this policy may result in serious consequences as outlined in Section 10.
                        </p>
                    </section>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
                    <a href="/register" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">‚Üê Back to Registration</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

